# Clean Architecture Rules

## Layer dependency direction
```
api → application → domain ← infrastructure
```
- `domain` has zero framework imports (no FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Redis)
- `application` depends only on `domain`; defines ports as `Protocol` classes
- `infrastructure` implements ports; imports SQLAlchemy, Redis, etc.
- `api` wires everything via FastAPI `Depends`

## Adding a new entity — checklist
See README "Adding a New Entity" section for the full step-by-step guide.
CI runs these checks automatically via `.github/workflows/ci.yml`.

Quick order:
1. `domain/entities/<entity>.py` — dataclass
2. `domain/value_objects/<vo>.py` — if needed
3. `domain/repositories/<entity>_repository.py` — Protocol
4. `domain/exceptions.py` — domain errors
5. `application/dto/<entity>.py` — DTOs
6. `application/mappers/<entity>.py` — entity ↔ DTO
7. `application/use_cases/<entity>/` — one file per use case
8. `infrastructure/db/models/<entity>.py` — ORM model
9. `infrastructure/repositories/<entity>_repository.py` — SQLAlchemy impl
10. `api/schemas/<entity>.py` — Pydantic request/response schemas
11. `api/v1/<entity>s.py` — router
12. `api/v1/router.py` — register the new router
13. `migrations/` — alembic revision
14. `tests/unit/domain/test_<entity>.py`
15. `tests/integration/api/test_<entity>s_flow.py`
